caption: I admire this venue very much. theres a romantic atmosphere. The meals are wonderful. the service is efficient and the waiters are well trained. The pay is fair. extremely recommend.

It's hard to mess up Thai food, but equally as hard is to stand out from the rest. Thai Chef Street Food stands out from the rest. A small shop along Connecticut Avenue Northwest in Dupont Circle, they offer takeout and safe pickup during the pandemic. And wow, it's tasty!  We ordered chicken green curry, panang curry, pad thai and drunken noodles and the flavors were bold in each dish. They also balance the spice well giving each dish a little kick without being too much.  We ordered online and our orders were ready right on time! Service is friendly.
Pad thai was excellent. So was the curry puffs. Only complain is the small curry puffs portion. Will order Again.
Nice food. Great  staff

Got the takeout order of Drunken Noodles w/ Tofu and Veggies from here via online order. Their pick up process was super easy and the takeout container was filled to the brim with food. Will be getting food from here again soon.
I ordered shrimp pad Thai and the curry puffs. Both were amazing and flavorful, but the curry puff was one of the best appetizers I’ve ever had. I highly recommend.

They serve a lot of vegetables with the dish. I ordered the kaprow duck and half of the dish was boiled vegetables. The mango sticky rice was somehow salty, the sticky rice was cooked long time ago so it lost the moisture. Great interior design though.
We ordered the vegetarian delight and drunken noodles — both were great!
I'd say it's the best Pad Thai in D.C.-- but the Panag curry was too sweet and the Bangkok wings were overly battered, rubbery and not crispy.

The food was fine, but they claim that you get 10% off by ordering on the phone, which we double checked and asked about before ordering on the phone, but I just looked at the receipt and of course they didn’t give the discount. I hate false advertising. Would have rather just paid for my food without the empty promise of a discount only to be left disappointed.

Really tasty Thai - we got the chicken pineapple fried rice, curry puffs and the chicken pad Thai. All were very good. The curry puff was a surprising highlight. Tons of flavor from the sweet basil sauce. The pad Thai was very flavorful and noodles were perfect. Fried rice was solid, would probably get something else next time but it was still tasty.

My roomies and I ordered a feast from Thai Chef last night. DAMN this place is good. The red curry had the perfect amount of heat, and the Curry Puffs were the best I’ve ever had. The pastry was so crispy and tasty. Everyone loved our food and was super impressed with Thai Chef.
Delicious curry !!! Loved it
Authentic Thai food just how you find it in the streets of Bangkok. I spent over 5 months in Thailand and I miss the food so much. Thai Chef brings me back to Bangkok every time! Great food!
Great people. Great food. Great experience every time. Thank you for getting me through 2020 with delicious Thai food!

Delicious and fresh. I sat at the bar and chatted with the bartender about his recommendations before choosing. I always get green papaya salad, and theirs is exceptional. Then I had the Kapow Gai Kai Dao, it was beautifully presented and spicy-tasty. The "Crazy Thai Lady" spin on a margarita was a good choice, too.
Amazing!! Treat yo self
Nothing special about the food, service is bad. The waiter are so unhappy to serve you. Not recommend.
Great food, from presentation to taste.. just perfect. Will definitely visit again!!!!  You guys are understaffed tho, that poor girl can't serve ten over tables on her own. Cmon guys!
The food was great and the service was solid too. All for a good price for DC. Nice atmosphere too. The drunken noodles were very tasty. Would come back again!
Delicious food! Even the classic dishes have a lot of flavor. The place is nicely decorated, and there are a lot of choices on the menu. Would recommend to a friend.
Authentic thai cuisine!!!
It's a great place to get your fix for thai food. Really good scenery inside and relaxing vibe.

This place is great. The cocktails are original and spot-on, and the food is delicious. Quick and nice service in a fun setting. Worth it for a meal, and the happy hour has good deals. Get the curry puffs!
The food and drinks here at absolutely great! Quaint little spot in DuPont, so if you can please make a reservation. Especially around the time of Happy Hour!

Bad customer service. My order was placed 40 mins ago. I called and asked right after placing it and the restaurant confirmed that they received it. I got here 40 mins later and the order was not placed. It was not prepared. Never coming back here. These people are liars.

Three servers and a bartender were on duty besides unseen kitchen staff. Service was slow at lunch time. We ordered right off the new menu. One person in our party ordered In Thai. The staff seemed more busy with their cellphones than with customers. Food was ok. I won’t go back & I used to enjoy it. I can’t speak for my 3 lunch companions. A flat 1 Star...
Food was excellent, service has room for Improvement
BEST THAI IN DC!! I have not tasted such robust flavors since my trip to Thailand. This is not your average pad Thai joint. The Thai street food is off the chain!
Overall good thai food.
Really great service, solid drinks, wonderful food.  Highly recommend!
Very good fixed price lunch. Make sure to ask for the specific menu, since they only handed us the a-la-carte menu before we said anything. Great value, we each had leftovers for the next day.
Finally a Thai place that understands us non-Thai types like it super hot too.
OMG! This is so good! The calimari is tender & delicious! I went in expecting a 3 and the meal is a 5!
Every dish I’ve had here is great! Will return.
The place offers a large variety of delicious food. I enjoy dining here. Employees are always kind, pricing is fair and the spot is always kept clean.

Love this place!!! Our drinks were incredible, I got a lemongrass infused tequila! The papaya salad was out of this world and my curry was perfect! They clearly have gluten-free items marked, service was outstanding! Highly recommend!
Excellent Thai food and fun atmosphere
Food was delicious, staff was super friendly and attentive and the ambiance is top notch. Definitely recommend for a casual night out
Awesome
(Translated by Google) Delicious dessert  (Original) Postre delicioso
Great Thai food and ask for some spices and they bring out a lot of great options for some added heat!

Terrible service. Took 20 mins for someone to come over, when they did, they acted like they didn’t want to talk to us. The hostess just sat there, made a face when we called her over.  Found hair in my food and my friends cup has a clear lip stain on her water cup. Yuck!  Drinks were good, reasonable happy hour deals.
Good and authentic thai food with flavors. Pleasant atmosphere and staff. At reasonable price.
Nice details in the design. Yummy Thai food!!
Great drinks, food, and service.
Loved the people!!

Food was very good, too bad for the service. After trying to get my plate away before being done, they were just trying to shovel down my neck the bill and kick me out of the restaurant. Worse is that the same happened to another customer right in front of me. Weird habits ...

Tom Ka soup was too sour. It lost the coconut flavor. Chicken satè was nice/basic/good. Bartender PK was great, very accommodating. He offered to remake the soup or to make it less sour next visit. I'll take him up on it! I've  had very nice experiences there.
Panang and psd Thai was spot on. Favorite was mango sticky rice. Coconut ice cream was the best we have ever had. We visited Thai land in March. We know our stuff!!
Great Thai food restaurant in the Dupont area
Good food, great cocktails!!
Decent food and friendly staff  Chicken fried rice was yummy

First off, the interior is incredible. Second, I asked for drink recommendations and the waitress did not disappoint. She asked for my flavor preferences and then pointed out two options. I got one, my boyfriend got the other, and they were PERFECT. Third, the food was delicious! Some of the best Thai food we've had. I highly recommend if you're on the DC area.

This place is basically mall Thai food. The service is spotty, food is below average, and the price doesn’t reflect the quality. With the northern Thai/Lao explosion happening in dc, there are a dozen better places to get Thai. However if you just want a generic sugary pad Thai, go here.
So yummy and great service
Pricey and just not that good for either drinks or food. Go to Regent or Thaiphoon instead.
Nice happy hour menu.

The food was delicious but what loved most (and don't have a picture of, darn) was the Thai iced tea. A great spot for a quick bite, drinks, or a full meal. I didn't sample any but they had a range of interesting home gin infusions that sounded delightful
Great, polite service.  Not as traditional as I was looking for. Food was good though.
Food was great!
Ordered uberEats here tonight. Got the Pad thai, shrimp bikini and the tom yum soup. Everything wassooooo good. So fresh and so very flavorful. Will be my go-to spot for Pad thai, now

Hands down the best Panang curry I’ve had, I’ve had it at about a dozen places around the country and the flavors are unparalleled here  Service is quick and great, it’s a gorgeous spot as well. It is a must try!
Very good food and Tea.
Good soups! Good service!
Tasty drinks but the green curry was disappointing. Not much flavor. Good level of heat in it though.
Absolutely loved this place!!! Delicious food and wonderful service!!
Chill environment. Good food with spicy options. Fantastic drinks. Great for group or solo dinning. Highly recommend.
Owner/bartender is cool and really knows her mixology. Food also impressed.
I'm from NY. I see a lot of Thai. Anyone who rates this place below 5 is a damn lier. Amazing drunks, amazing staff, incredible food.
Solid Thai food spot in the DUPont Area
I like  the exotic  cold drinks. They accommodated  our large party efficiently.
What a cool spot for sure coming back. Great cocktails and food. Our server was kind and attentive. We anticipate being back for more. Cheers
Great food, drinks and ambience. Very casual. Good prices.
Excellent, fresh Thai food.
Came for a on-break bite. Great ambiance, staff are super friendly & great cocktails. Perfect for the spring/summer time!
Some of the best Thai food I’ve had! Really cute environment and reasonable prices.
Really wanted to like this place, but the Hainan chicken was beyond dry. Liked the fried tofu and the rice that came with the chicken was flavorful.

Service was 👍. Servicer uses time productivity. Although manu and bathroom 🚪 was dirty. I saw people cleaning. 5 stars because the food tasted amazing ! A lot of bold flavors. I got a 🍲 with minced chicken at 1st the look didn't impress me however the taste far surpassed my expectations. Everything tasted original. Prices were o.k. and could be climbing on the high side. Google accurately had it at $$.  many people came in asking for deserts. But none were offered while I was there. Will recommend !!!
Amazing food
I absolutely adore this place! The food is always fantastic and the waiters/waitresses are quite helpful! Anyone who is craving some delicious Thai food should come here!
Service was very lackluster. Food was decent, but portions were small for the price. Forgettable.
Simply lovely! Everything so novel yet authentic! Check out the mango sticky rice~ how can you not love that? We will be back trying out the rainbow unicorn popcorn.
Really liked the old place, the missed the mark on staples that they used to do really well. Worth trying again service was very good.

I love this place! I had it atleast two or three times during my DC trip. Really good food and drinks. I never ran into a crowd. Food didnt take long to cook. Staff was very nice. Its located in a really good walking area right outside of DuPont Circle.
The fish dishes, shrimp, drinks, and Thai waffle we're good. Not a fan of their papaya salad
Drunken noodles were delicious! Very happy I found this restaurant. Will be back!

HIGHLY RECOMMENDED! Honestly I'm usually skeptical of Thai places because they've become oversaturated in my neighborhood, but we knew we were in for some awesome food when we saw lots of Thai students in there for lunch.  The vibe is eclectic and lots of fun. The food is fantastic and really emphasized the street food aspect to encourage you to treat yourself to new items that you don't find on standard Thai menus. Of course there are familiar items, but if it's your first time here, try something you won't get somewhere else!  Oh and the plating is gorgeous! Every dish came out and it looked like time was spent putting it on the plate. Of course the best was dessert! Mango sticky rice! Beautiful! And it was SO GOOD! The rice was still warm under the cool and exactly rip mango slices!  It goes without saying that the staff of great too! I'd definitely like to come back to see the dinner service and see the place transformed at night.
Food is delicious, excellent location, drinks are fun, prices are fair, decor is awesome. "Two chilis" on the menu is moderately spicy and will give you moderate problems the next morning.
Great food and atmosphere! The crying tiger steak was amazing

If you order Calamari don't expect tentacles... I was upset and was really disappointed but excited for this place..just to find out that I won't get the full Calamari dish.. so yes 3 stars. I ordered the Calamari and the Bangkok wings and they all taste the same and look the same ..even tho there are only 2 kinds.. that alone deserves 2 stars at best..🙄

I ordered fried chicken, shrimp, pineapple rice. It was not too bad but it was like warmed up in a microwave,  pineapples were too hot while some part of chicken was almost cold. I am a bit dissappointed with my dish
Awesome place. Great food and the service is phenomenal.
Yummy like as Thai style!!! Waffle is awesome.
Excellent meal! Panang curry was great.
The food is pretty decent. There are some genuine Thai recipes in the mix. The service was good. The new decor is very nice. It is a good place to go with friends.

We just went for happy hour cocktails. I got a lichee tini, while my wife got a sake martini. They were both so delicious and only $5! Yet despite being such a bargain, they were both strong. We had dinner reservations elsewhere so we didn’t get food, but it all looked and smelled amazing, and the people around us really enjoyed their food. We will definitely be back for more drinks and food too.

(Translated by Google) The striking and lively decoration makes the visit to this restaurant very pleasant. The food is rich and taken care of and the prices very reasonable. The daily menus are tasty and well served.  (Original) La llamativa y viva decoración hace que la visita a este restaurante sea muy agradable. La comida es rica y cuidada y los precios muy razonables. Los menús del día son sabrosos y bien servidos.
Very quick service, friendly staff, delicious food. Their homemade strawberry lemonade is easily the best I've ever had.
(Translated by Google) Cozy and warm restaurant. The food is delicious and varied. I recommend !  (Original) Restaurant cosy et chaleureux. La nourriture est délicieuse et variée. Je recommande !
Kevin’s great.

Tasty curry puffs but the drunken noodles were quite flavorless. It was a nasty surprise to eat a bit and then realize half the takeout box was actually iceberg lettuce, added presumably to give the illusion of a larger portion.
Gaudy atmosphere, bad food. Pushy waitstaff, and I felt rushed to leave even though I was a paying customer. Would not recommend for anything more than a quick drink, skip it.

This place was getting put on blast on Instagram and I was excited to try it for myself. My anticipation was followed by disappointment. Tom Yum soup was the only hit for me despite its small size. Grilled squid was a generous portion but lacked flavor. Drunken noodles weren't anything special. I'd reconsider this maybe for a lazy Sunday dinner delivery. The DC foodie scene over hyped this one.
They have a very good lunch here, with a flavorful chicken Panang.  It wasn't spicy enough, but it was tasty.  The Thai coffee was also very good.
Loved it, just came through for lunch special and I already expect overcooked chicken in that soup. Pleasantly surprised not the case here.
I had a falafel, never had one before, delicious. The sauce was a bit spicy for me but I would get it again
Authentic thai food. Service was great...food was well flavored. Great place to eat!
Great food. The bubble waffle must be tried.

(Translated by Google) We are fan of Thai cuisine and here is our good address on Washington on: Thai chef street food  Do you want to eat soups, kebabs, ...? So, go to the side of this address!  Let yourself be charmed by the cuisine of the "Thai chef street food".  Thai cuisine is obviously the specialty of the restaurant. The restaurant is particularly known for skewered chicken skewers and street food dishes à la carte.  In terms of seating, the restaurant can accommodate +/- 30 people on a service. The staff will be happy to welcome you in English. The property accepts cash and Carte B as payment methods.  (Original) Nous sommes fan de cuisine Thai et voici notre bonne adresse sur Washington le : Thaï chef street food  Vous avez envie de manger les soupes, des brochettes,... ? Alors, passez du côté de cette adresse !  Laissez-vous charmer par la cuisine du  "Thaï chef street food".  Le cuisine thaï est évidement la spécialité du restaurant. Le restaurant est notamment connu pour les brochettes de poulet sauce saté et ses plats de street food proposés à la carte.  En termes de couverts, le restaurant peut accueillir +/- 30 personnes sur un service. Le personnel de l'établissement sera ravi de vous accueillir en anglais. L'établissement accepte le cash et la Carte B comme moyens de paiement.
Trendy/chic place with great food and surprisingly good cocktails. Will definitely be back!!

The Thai lady in the front has an attitude. I walked in and nobody greeted me. The food was okay but not great. Big disappointment. I was charged 2Dollars extra for the small side of hot sauce that I asked for because the food I ordered wasn’t spicy enough. Usually restaurant never charge for hot sauce.  The smoothie drink I ordered was horrible and unreasonable price. It was served in a small glass size like as a tall Starbucks cup size with $5.95 and its taste was horrible. No flavor at all.  I left 2 stars because the food I ordered was good. The service overall was very disappointing and because of that,,, I will never be back again.
Finally a thai place that actually serves thai food
Great food. Great service.  Doesn't take too long either.  Reasonable pricing.
Great food at reasonable prices.
Ordered vegetarian meal.  Came with chicken soup and the main dish was cooked in fish sauce.... and the veggies were clearly from cans.   I like the paint-job, so 2- Stars.
Good food. I had red curry and the fried bananas and ice cream for dessert. We sat at the bar and the bartender was attentive and made good recommendations.
Very tasty food. Server appeared to be learning still, but very attentive. Quirky decor. Overall great experience. Would recommend and return.
I Highly recommend this restaurant! Delicious food, great prices and really cool atmosphere.

I stumbled upon this place in the pouring rain and was so glad that I did! Between the street food options, tropical cocktails and dessert bar this place is definitely on point with it's theme. I was disappointed by how few vegetarian options there were since Thai food is quite veg friendly itself, but since I was going for drinks & dessert it still did the trick. Try the lychee martini!
Food was very good. Had the drunken noodles.. the tea was also good not too sweet
Great food, good taste!

What a great restaurant! We walked in and were immediately greeted by their hostess and wonderful workers. They were very charming and super nice. Their interior consisted of neat collections of small items and cool lights. It felt quite cozy to eat there.  We ordered from their lunch specials as we ate there around 1 o'clock. I got the Spicy Basil Fried Rice with chicken/pork and also ordered the Thai Ice Tea. They were really flexible with my Ice Tea - I was hesitant of ordering the tea because of my dairy allergy. But they worked with my allergy and replaced the milk with lemonade. Again, super nice!  The tea was a little too sweet for me but it was still really delicious. Next time I would definitely ask them to tone down on the sugar level.  I love their lunch specials! It comes with the entree, a spring roll, and soup. The soup came first and it was mixed with chicken and mushrooms. All together it tasted sour and spicy which was really good. Then our entrees came out and again, I got the Spicy Basil Fried Rice with chicken/pork. It also came with the spring roll on the side. Needless to say, it was all yummy. The meat wasn't dry at all and the portions were huge. It was pretty spicy so next time I come, I'll tell them to lower the spice level.  After our food, we ordered their deserts. I got the raspberry slush. It was nice and cold. I could chew on the small icicles in it which I really like. It was great for the hot summer day after our meal.  I got to know the owner who was extremely friendly. She, in addition to our waitress, constantly checked on us to make sure we were doing ok.  It was a great experience and I'll definitely be back. Highly recommend this place.
Excellent tasty Thai food. Very good reception.
Crunchy fried banana with coconut ice cream is the absolute best mix of flavors and textures in a dessert you could possibly have!!!

We made the mistake of arriving at 9pm... an hour before closing time. We were almost literally encouraged to leave just before 10, then at 10, when asking for toothpicks, it was like yes they are over there next to the exit. They kept coming to take our dishes even though we were still eating. Definitely rude- too bad won’t be going there anymore.
I loved the ice tea
Spicy fried rice is great. Service and value also very good.
Bad

I have to say, I had a wonderful experience at Thai Chef. I ordered the Drunken Noodles, something I always order when I go to Thai restaurants and it was delicious! Also, I met the owner who was extremely friendly and welcoming.  Another thing I like is the ambience and decor of the shop, it really feels like I’m in a street market.  Love the place, will be coming back :)
The won tons were very good, the papaya salad was better and the panang was awesome.
Excellent Thai food with true courtesy and kindness. Highly recommended...
Great place to beat the summer heat!! I ordered coconut ice cream with mochi, lychee and wafer toppings! The ice cream was delicious.
Nice place.  The full, open window to the street was sun excellent feature. I ordered a nicely made, tasty Mai Thai.
Great authentic Thai food.
Mediocre Thai food.
Fun place good food
Service was a little lacking, but the food was excellent. As the name suggests, a menu full of great Thai street food classics.
Some of the Best Thai food around! Their panang and pad cashew are a must!!
Food was great and staff was awesome!
Awesome Prices and delicious food! It is a 4.9 Star restaurant
This place used to be my favorite Thai and Sushi place. They sold the place to a new owner and this place has changed a lot. Their sushi rice tasted sour and their wasabi is dyed horseradish.
Amazing spicy drunken noodles! And the sushi was very nice!
Good lunch options, tasty big portions.
Authentication Thai food
Great food. Authenticity service
Great authenticity
Good food. Good service
Me and my husband loved this place it was good ! Would go back again ! We love Thai Food !

Very good Thai food at an affordable price.  The lunch special has lots of little extras.  Service is very good.  The place did have a number of unusual odors qafting around, not all of then pleasant, but nothing out of line for a good restaurant.
The main person at front was not nice at all. The person who cleaned up the tables was very nice The food was jus average
Thumb up for decorations and foods. I’ve been there many times and tried different foods. Everything is so yummy and also they’re serving sushi. Recommend for this place if u like thai food !!!
Best papaya salad I’ve ever had!!!
This kind of food is what Thai people actually eat in Bangkok. Need I say more?
super great food and friendly staff. I love their street food menu! Can't wait to come back and try more street food!
(Translated by Google) Good food  (Original) God mat
They recently renovated!  Food was delicios and customer service out of this world!👌
Very good food. And extremly friendly personal.

I'm sooooo sad because this used to be my FAVORITE happy hour sushi spot in DC. They got new management and downsized the dinner and sushi menu thus getting rid of a lot of my favorites.  If this had been a few months ago it would have gotten a full 5/5 stars
Outstanding lunch specials for $12.99. We had the broad rice noodles and panang curry.  Outstanding!

UPDATES REVIEW: 7.17  They changed owners and this is first time I've been back since and it was a major disappointment. I've loved this place for years but my lord is this place different for all the wrong reasons, The menu staples I loved are gone and even the drinks taste different. I'm super disappointed this happened but good  Would give this place 5 stars - my favorite place for sushi in DC, but sometimes the service is a little off. The happy hour is great - drinks are heavy handed - less than perfect service is worth it to me.

The food was absolutely amazing. The lunch special came with soup, a fried spring roll, and I got the green curry which was divine. It was a lovely lunch spot with my program mates, definitely recommend going here with other folks!
Good happy hour menu. Nice servers.  Still need to check out the dinner menu.
Excellent Sushi & seating arrangement.
I had a great experience at Thai Chef. The food was delicious, staff was amazing, overall great time.
This review is only for sushi, which is really mushie and pretty sloppy.

My husband and I had a quick visit at dupoint circle and was looking for a resto that offered thai/asian food for dinner. We ate there and it was the best food I tasted in Washington and the ginger ale was a perfect combination.

I wasn't looking for a fancy sushi spot but just a quick lunch bite during work. I ordered the California Roll & Crunchy Salmon Roll and I couldn't get through the second bite. The California Roll was filled with more fish eggs than you can imagine than avocado and crab. The salmon in the crunchy roll tasted like it had been left out for days. I was also surprised that I was charged $3.00 for Green Tea, an item that usually is serviced and available for free. Maybe I should've stuck to ordering Thai but besides the nice service, I wouldn't recommend this for a sushi spot :(.
Love the Happy Hour Mai Tai! I actually sought out this place, after serendipitously discovering it when visiting DC last summer. Today tried the spicy avocado roll with peanuts. Delicious!
Super cheap happy hour, sushi quality corresponds, Thai dishes are good though
I love the Thai food here.  Everything is clean and fresh.  The service is fast and never rushing you.  I will definitely eat here again.
I ate the ramen noodles with chicken, it was yummy. It is located close to DuPont metro. To my surprise it had two floors.
Excellent food!
A go-to sushi place for me and my friends in DC.

I really didn't enjoy my order from here - based on the reviews I was pretty disappointed.  I did pickup and the process was easy and fast. I felt the fish wasn't fresh, though the portions were good. There were a few pieces that tasted like soap that I could not stomach.  I also ordered a chicken and eggplant dish that tasted very sour and I did not save the leftovers. Everything was fast and cooked through, but with so many options nearby I will not be back.  The pad Thai was actually pretty tasty - there was plentiful shrimp and good flavor, so order this if you come here!
Not the best Thai food I've ever had.
One of my favorite sushi spots. I haven't had many of their other dishes, but the drunken noodles are also pretty good.
I've been going to this restaurant since my early days in college in the 80s... The neighborhood has changed. But I still love this restaurant.
Great HH
Great food and drinks
Pineapple Shrimp Fried Rice is amazing!
Good deal for happy hour from 5pm-7pm. You can get the drink in $4.
The food is pretty good. The service is mediocre. Their special rolls are the best. Definitely recommend trying them.

I had the cellophane noodle dish. It was good but not super spicy. My BF had the chicken kaprow. The chicken was the way he liked it - thinly sliced. The sauce was too light though and beware it comes with broccoli.

Favorite sushi place in the city. Great happy hour prices ($6 rolls), fresh sushi, and Leechitini ($4)! Try the Thai Chef roll it's amazing, also the NY roll with fresh salmon is so great! If you are not a sushi person their Thai food is also great!
Acceptable service and food quality. No complaints. Great for a casual, reasonably priced evening out.
Although this is Thai, the sushi is outstanding.
Great happy hour menu and great drinks worth trying.

Had the seaweed salad - a bit dry, but the seaweed was fresh and crunchy. Ordered two rolls (yellowtail/scallion and eel avocado). Both were mediocre. For the price, there's better, but it was decent sushi. They'd be wise to invest in better chopsticks for dine in ordering as well.
Two words: Duck kraprow. Best Thai dish in DC in my humble opinion.

We been going to this place even before the renovation.  They use to have these box table displays so it looked like you were eating above a casket.  It much more modern and trendy looking as other Thai places now.  Since moving to NYC I think I've been spoiled by the Thai food up there.  Overall, it is turns out decent Thai food.  My rule of thumb is places that do two different type of cuisine (sushi) usually churn out mediocre food.  I tend to like Thaitantic better on 14th which serves more 'authentic' cuisine and only Thai food. Overall all they do keep us going back as one of the good ol stand by when I'm in town and in the Dupont Circle area.
The food is pretty good and the price is just about right but nothing here blows you away.

Awful place. Weird atmosphere, disgusting dirty and undercooked food! I dislike other Thai places on DuPont,  but this place is the worst ever, King of disaster!!! I have no idea why special health department does not close it down:(

I've been going to Thai Chef for a number of years and have always found it a solid neighborhood choice. I prefer it for lunch as it can get loud at dinner time. The curry dishes are great (green, red) and the sushi choices are excellent.
Delicious & extremely prompt!
It's horrible. It was very loud. I wasn't able to have a conversation without yelling. the food looked bad and the sushi I occasionally pick up boxxed from the grocery store is better quality.

I am so ashamed of having my friends go to this place for their last evening in DC. THIS WAS AWFUL! The sushi was OK, This place was good to me because It was the first time I had sushi about three years ago and Since I fell in love with it back then, I wanted my friends to enjoy it as well. BOY WAS I WRONG. The services was terrible!!! First I could not understand one word the woman was saying, I asked about plates and she was no help! We ordered the FRIED RICE with steak and it was delicious so we thought hey, the sushi will be good. THE ROLLS WERE SOOOO BIG they did not fit in our mouths!!! We asked if our friend could buy avocado for his fried rice and he was told the avocado would be THREE DOLLARS PER SLICE, YES NOT ONE AVOCADO PER SLICE WE ASKED TWICE! The server took forever I mean FOREVER, to bring back my friends sushi, we literally ate our rice and then he came back with those huge rolls of TEMPURA, which by the way only had tempura shrimp inside and big pieces of lettuce, I almost thought I was a rabbit. SO WHEN IT CAME TIME TO PAY, THE SERVER CAME BACK TO THE TABLE TO ASK WHY HE HAD GOTTEN THAT TIP. Guilty pleasure Thai Food when we're too lazy to cook at home.  They deliver to a very small part of NW DC for free if you spend 20 or more...staff is not particularly friendly even though they recognize us and know our order.  The Green Curry is amazing, a bit spicy and pretty authentic for a place that sells chinese, japanese, and thai food.  Best Thai food in Dupont...
Awesome Kaprow Duck

A pretty run of the mill Asian joint. It says Thai on the sign and they do have a large selection of Thai dishes, but they also serve up some really interesting sounding sushi rolls and have a small sushi bar against the wall in addition to the tables. The high ceilings alleviate the crowded feeling due to the proximity of the tables and at night it could almost pass for intimate with the low lighting if you're along the wall. The food wouldnt bring me back, but the speed at which it came out was astounding and would definitely make this a great spot for weekday lunch.
Good, fast service; the drunken noodles were also decent and seemed to have a little more character than most places.
Good solid sushi! I had the Bangkok Roll and the Maryland Roll and it was delicious!

Thai Chef is a reliable, affordable place for sushi.  It is not going to knock your socks off but it is an honest good-value spot.  The sushi is always fresh, the portions generous (by contrast with Sushi Taro) and the staff are extremely conscientious, hard-working and efficient.  You will not feel like you have spent an hour in a Japanese ryokan but you also will not feel like you have been ripped off.
